'''Peter Mikhailovich Bogaevsky''' (or Bogayevsky) (({{lang-ru|Пётр Михайлович Богаевский}}) (({{lang-bg|Петър Михайлович Богаевски}}) (January 23, 1866 — January 29, 1929)<ref name="russkayagazeta">{{cite web |url=http://russkayagazeta.com/rg/gazeta/fullstory/russian-tomb-15/ |title=РУССКАЯ ГАЗЕТА № 15/2006: Незабытые могилы - духовный мемориал зарубежным соотечественникам |format= |work=russkayagazeta.com |accessdate=2009-08-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060515132534/http://russkayagazeta.com/rg/gazeta/fullstory/russian-tomb-15/ |archivedate=2006-05-15 |df= }}</ref> was a professor of international law in the Russian Empire. He was a professor at [[Tomsk State University|Tomsk University]] and later at [[Kiev University]] where he founded and directed the Kiev Institute for Near East.<ref name = "Directory">{{cite book | title = Directory of Russian educators, research specialists and scientists now living in Europe | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=fkPPAAAAMAAJ | publisher = Institute of International Education|pages = 6 | location = New York | year = 1929}}</ref> Following the [[Socialist revolution]], he fled as an emigre to [[Sofia, Bulgaria]] where he assumed the post of professor of [[international law]] at the [[University of Sofia]]. With [[Stefan Bobchev]] he founded the [[University of National and World Economy|Free University of Political and Economic Science]].<ref name="russkayagazeta"/><ref name="urlУниверситет за национално и световно стопанство">{{cite web |url=http://www.unwe.acad.bg/?page_id=4 |title=Университет за национално и световно стопанство |format= |work= |accessdate=2009-08-29}}</ref> It was then also known as the ''Balkan Institute of the Near East'', and was a private, but state-recognized institute which drew on the [[Ecole des Sciences Politiques]] as a model, and offered courses in diplomatic and consular services, administration and finance, and other areas.<ref name = "Social sciences">{{cite book | title = Social sciences in the Balkans and in Turkey: a survey of resources for study and research in these fields of knowledge |author = Robert Joseph Kerner| url = https://books.google.com/books?id=92BMAAAAIAAJ&q=%22balkan+institute+of+the+near+east%22&dq=%22balkan+institute+of+the+near+east%22 | publisher = University of California Press |pages = 87 | location = | year = 1930}}</ref><ref name = "School and Society">{{cite journal | title =School and Society |author = | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=sVUw3kfQdM4C&q=%22balkan+institute+of+the+near+east%22&dq=%22balkan+institute+of+the+near+east%22 |journal = School and Society | publisher= Society for the Advancement of Education |pages = 249 | volume = 39 | year = 1934}}</ref>
